<subSubSection box="[1215,1745,439,535]" pageId="0" pageNumber="242" type="vernacular_names">(TREESHREWS)</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="242" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1231,2114,607,1238]" pageId="0" pageNumber="242">• Small terrestrial to arboreal generalist foragers, typically olivaceous brown but some with bright pelage on upperparts and tails, nearly all with pale markings on shoulders; many adaptable to anthropogenic disturbance.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6779162" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6779162" box="[1232,1422,764,797]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6779162/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="242" startId="0.[1232,1245,764,797]" targetBox="[1355,1992,818,1006]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1231,2114,607,1238]" box="[1232,1422,764,797]" pageId="0" pageNumber="242">• 20-45 cm.</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1231,2114,607,1238]" pageId="0" pageNumber="242">• Indo-Malayan Region, marginally into Palearctic Region. •</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1231,2114,607,1238]" pageId="0" pageNumber="242">• Mostly tropical rainforests but also scrub jungle; montane, evergreen, and deciduous forests; plantations.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1231,2114,607,1238]" box="[1232,1706,1154,1192]" pageId="0" pageNumber="242">• 3 genera, 22 species, 47 taxa.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1231,2114,607,1238]" box="[1232,1994,1199,1232]" pageId="0" pageNumber="242">• 2 species Endangered; none Extinct since 1600.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
